{
  "name": "ultracode-dynamic-workflow-codex",
  "version": "3.4.0",
  "created_at_utc": "2026-06-14T15:03:33.069825+00:00",
  "skill_name": "ultracode",
  "activation": "$ultracode only",
  "notes": "PACKAGE_MANIFEST.json excludes itself from the file hash list.",
  "primary_changes": [
    "uc_route.py + uc_bootstrap.py: probe run-dir writability up front and emit a clean one-line JSON 'run-dir-not-writable' error (exit 3) instead of a multi-line pathlib traceback when the sandbox denies writes.",
    "Non-overlapping subagent lanes: doc_mapper=docs/config truth-sources, mapper=source-code capability, test_mapper=verification maturity, reviewer=security/compliance/IP (the scoring role). Enforced in agent TOML developer_instructions, bootstrap work-item objectives, and SKILL.md, so a fan-out is complementary instead of N duplicate audits.",
    "Result schema splits two axes: status = execution (ok|blocked|error), verdict = judgment (pass|concerns|fail|not-applicable). Updated across all agent TOMLs, SKILL.md, uc_bootstrap spawn prompt, and uc_adversarial_verify spawn prompt; resolves the 'reviewer=fail vs others=ok' false-divergence.",
    "uc_merge_results.py: dedups findings across workers into one inventory (collapses identical claims, lists all corroborating sources, keeps top severity) and surfaces verdict counts; claims.csv gains a 'sources' column.",
    "(prior) os.walk traversal budget/pruning fix for slow mounts; task-aware Stop gate (verification_skip.json); Codex-only .codex install; hookSpecificOutput-wrapper output shape; standalone profile; content-aware gates; cross-platform uninstall."
  ],
